<PageLayout title="Fullstack Engineer — Windward Labs" description="Join Windward Labs as a Fullstack Engineer.">
  <h1>Fullstack Engineer</h1>

  <h2>Responsibilities</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Working across our product portfolio to deliver clean, scalable, and maintainable code</li>
    <li>Working closely with customers to deliver delightful experiences and securely move millions of dollars onchain</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Projects you may work on</h2>
  <p><strong>Farcaster Mini-Apps:</strong> We use Farcaster as a go-to-market channel for many of our onchain products and experiences. You will help us develop our suite of products to be compatible with the Farcaster ecosystem and maintain shared infrastructure across applications.</p>
  <p><strong>Ethereum Marketplaces:</strong> We are deeply interested in developing modern, efficient markets for users to buy and sell tokens. You will help us write scalable indexers and data stores, develop intuitive frontends, and integrate secure smart contracts to facilitate hundreds of millions of dollars in volume.</p>

  <h2>About you</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>You are impatient to solve problems and don't wait for experts. If you see an issue, you solve it yourself.</li>
    <li>You have 5+ years of experience writing software and working in a team based environment to deliver production applications.</li>
    <li>You have experience maintaining availability on websites that receive millions of visitors per month.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Backend: Node.js, Postgres, Redis, Solidity</li>
    <li>Infrastructure: Heroku, Vercel, Ethereum</li>
    <li>Frontend: Typescript React</li>
    <li>Design: Figma, v0</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Culture and Compensation</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>High-integrity, low-ego team.</li>
    <li>Flexible hours within a US based timezone. We work in Pacific Time most weeks.</li>
    <li>Salary USD $180k – $200k plus 0.5% – 1.5% equity.</li>
    <li>Health/vision/dental.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>About the role</h2>
  <p>You are our first technical hire, reporting directly to the founders, and you will shape engineering processes for products that move hundreds of millions of dollars through the Ethereum ecosystem.</p>
  <p>Five-plus years of production experience and a record of maintaining high-traffic sites are required. Remote-US preferred.</p>

  <h2>About Windward Labs</h2>
  <p>Windward Labs is a creative agency that delivers software and physical experiences to elevate the next generation of onchain creators. We are deeply optimistic and believe that a small group of people can make an outsized impact on the world through their work.</p>

  <h2>Interview Process</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Phone Call:</strong> 30 minute conversation with Phil to discuss the role, your background, and any questions you may have</li>
    <li><strong>Technical Call:</strong> 30 minute conversation with Jeff to learn about your technical background and area of expertise</li>
    <li><strong>Work Trial:</strong> 1 week paid work trial to ship real code in a production setting and learn about how you work and solve problems.</li>
  </ol>

